n\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ugh1665703129789.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ugh1665703129789.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ugh1665703129789.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ugh1665703129789\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      trigger validate (Field)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">System trigger that defines the procedural checks to validate a modified field.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ugh1665703129789__section_w2958ab1b7b1_w2959ab1b7_w2960ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ugh1665703129789__table_d14348e1_d14349e1_d14350e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Declaration: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">trigger validate</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Applies to: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lym1665702585074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lym1665702585074.html\" title=\"A Field is a Development Object that represents a unit of data in an Entity. This could represent a column in a DBMS table or data that is not stored in the database, such as a derived field or a user interface control. Its associated properties define the way it is stored, its GUI representation, and default behavior.\">Field</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Activation: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Activated during explicit or implicit\n                        validation: <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ugh1665703129789__li_d44381e1_d44382e1_d44383e1\">Explicitly, by validation\n                              statements (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validate</span>,\n                                 <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validateocc</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validatekey</span>, or\n                                 <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validatefield</span>) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ugh1665703129789__li_d44384e1_d44385e1_d44386e1\">Implicitly, during a\n                                 <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span> statement. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ugh1665703129789__li_d44387e1_d44388e1_d44389e1\">Implicitly, after the declarative\n                              checks, and in forms, prior to the field-level loseFocus trigger.\n                           </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default behavior: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> If no ProcScript is present in this trigger,\n                        there is no action; <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>,\n                           <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldvalidation</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldcheck</span>\n                        are set to 0. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Behavior upon completion: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> If <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> is less than\n                        zero, validation is considered to have failed and the field-level error\n                        trigger is activated. If it is greater than or equal to zero, validation is\n                        considered to have completed successfully. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ugh1665703129789__section_w2961ab1b7b3_w2962ab1b7_w2963ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d930130e172\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ugh1665703129789__p_d116657e1_d116658e1_d116659e1\">The field-level validate trigger defines the\n            procedural checks that are done to validate a modified field.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ugh1665703129789__p_d116660e1_d116661e1_d116662e1\">Validation is performed only if the field is marked\n            as modified (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldmod</span> is 1) and still requires validation\n               (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldvalidation</span> is 1) or if <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldcheck</span> is\n            1.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ugh1665703129789__p_d116663e1_d116664e1_d116665e1\">Because the validation statements\n               (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validatefield</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validatekey</span>,\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validateocc</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validate</span>) activate the\n            validation triggers (validate and validateKey), these statements should be used with\n            caution within the validation triggers.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"ugh1665703129789__note_w2967ab1b7b3b9_w2968ab1b7b3_w2969ab1b7_w2970ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> The\n            field-level validate trigger should not be used to modify the value being validated,\n            only to check whether a value is valid or not.</div>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">In the following example, a function that validates the bank account\n               number is called:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger validate ; of field BANK_ACCOUNT_NUMBER\n;verify that the bank account numbers conforms with the standard\ncall CHECK_ACCOUNT_NUMBER(BANK_ACCOUNT_NUMBER.CLIENT)\nreturn ($status)\nend; validate</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lcw1665702604012.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ProcScript for Data Validation</a><p>ProcScript instructions can be used to explicitly validate data, set validation conditions, check modification and validation status, and handle errors.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kgi1665702560769.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>store</a><p>Initiate validation and storage of all occurrences marked as modified. It activates the appropriate validation triggers as required, followed by the write and delete triggers.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wbv1665702600112.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger loseFocus (Field)</a><p>Trigger that defines what happens after a user successfully leaves a field in a form component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvb1665703130778.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger store</a><p>Trigger that responds to a request to save (store) the data.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/frh1665703129863.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger validateKey</a><p>System trigger that defines the procedural checks to validate a modified primary or candidate key.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iwi1665702603846.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger validate (Entity)</a><p>System trigger for validating entity occurrences.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616289\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616289\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "trigger validate (Field) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 trigger validate (Field) System trigger that defines the procedural checks to validate a modified field. Declaration: trigger validate Applies to: Field Activation: Activated during explicit or implicit validation: Explicitly, by validation statements ( validate , validateocc , validatekey , or validatefield ) Implicitly, during a store statement. Implicitly, after the declarative checks, and in forms, prior to the field-level loseFocus trigger. Default behavior: If no ProcScript is present in this trigger, there is no action; $status , $fieldvalidation , and $fieldcheck are set to 0. Behavior upon completion: If $status is less than zero, validation is considered to have failed and the field-level error trigger is activated. If it is greater than or equal to zero, validation is considered to have completed successfully. Description The field-level validate trigger defines the procedural checks that are done to validate a modified field. Validation is performed only if the field is marked as modified ( $fieldmod is 1) and still requires validation ( $fieldvalidation is 1) or if $fieldcheck is 1. Because the validation statements ( validatefield , validatekey , validateocc , and validate ) activate the validation triggers (validate and validateKey), these statements should be used with caution within the validation triggers. CAUTION: The field-level validate trigger should not be used to modify the value being validated, only to check whether a value is valid or not. In the following example, a function that validates the bank account number is called: trigger validate ; of field BANK_ACCOUNT_NUMBER ;verify that the bank account numbers conforms with the standard call CHECK_ACCOUNT_NUMBER(BANK_ACCOUNT_NUMBER.CLIENT) return ($status) end; validate Copy Related Links ProcScript for Data Validation ProcScript instructions can be used to explicitly validate data, set validation conditions, check modification and validation status, and handle errors. store Initiate validation and storage of all occurrences marked as modified. It activates the appropriate validation triggers as required, followed by the write and delete triggers. trigger loseFocus (Field) Trigger that defines what happens after a user successfully leaves a field in a form component. trigger store Trigger that responds to a request to save (store) the data. trigger validateKey System trigger that defines the procedural checks to validate a modified primary or candidate key. trigger validate (Entity) System trigger for validating entity occurrences. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}